作者: 烈火(fire)
题目: structure of base system.
日期: Thu Jan 27 19:36:06 2000
Here is the structure of the base system.
1 The different type of bases will be recorded in a simple daemon
  /daemons/base_d.c (BASE_D).It will replace current stuff_d.c. This
  daemon will hanlde the regist of all bases.
2 For the detailed information, such as the requriment to build this
  type of base, of each different type of base will be hold by seperate
  daemons. all these daemons will inherit from one typical base requirement
  daemon. The advantage of this method is that it is easier to coding.
  The disadvantage is hard to maintain when the number of base increase.
  Another solution is make the BASE_D to handle all the information.
3 An instance of a base is like a home for a player, it has many different
  function rooms and has npc working there. For each area, we will use a 
  seperate file to record its base information. the location will be in
  /data/area/base/xxx.o
4 A base_master will be used to create all the virtual rooms of bases.
  the localtion for base_master is /sgdomain/base/base_master.c
5 In order to save system resource, players only with job in base can enter
  a base. and once he finish his job, should leave the base immediately. and
  when the system find there is no players in the base, all the virtual room
  should be destoried and release the resource.
6 In the first step, a base will be created in nowhere, a player can
use certain
  command to enter the base and leave. later we may put the location of a base
  in the warmap. so in the war, if enemy troop enter that cell, the base will
  got some damage and so on
7 a base can generate many different events and a players can have many tasks
  in a base :)
8 In the first step, we may just try farm (on type of base ). After
it is successful
  an area will not create food unless it has farms.


